data.name: Grilled Teriyaki Chicken with Coconut Rice and Steamed Broccoli
data.quickTastyDescription: Deliciously grilled chicken marinated in a sweet teriyaki sauce, served with creamy coconut rice and fresh steamed broccoli. A perfect balance of flavors and textures!
detailedCookingInstructions: Marinate the chicken breasts in teriyaki sauce for at least 15 minutes.
In a medium saucepan, combine jasmine rice, coconut milk, and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 15 minutes or until rice is cooked.
While the rice is cooking, heat olive oil in a grill pan over medium-high heat.
Remove chicken from marinade and grill for about 6-7 minutes on each side until cooked through and nicely charred.
Steam the broccoli florets in a steamer basket over boiling water for about 5-7 minutes until tender.
Serve the grilled chicken with coconut rice and steamed broccoli on the side. Garnish with sesame seeds if desired.
